TECHNICAL EXPERT ORE FLOW OPERATIONS
Information:
Posted: 29 Apr 2014
Apply deadline: 28 Jul 2014
Location: Indonesia
Company: .
Job description:
Job Description:
The incumbent will provideassistance and expertise in directing and controlling Ore Flow and WasteCrushing operations and projects activities to the Ore Flow Operations Management team. They willmaximize production within the budget, in a timely, safe and environmentally friendly manner.
Additional responsibilities:
Promote safety and environmental awareness to all employees in his department to minimize accidents andenvironmental damage.
Provide expertise and support to review, inspect and promote SOP's for safety practices and safety awareness toensure a safe working environment and eliminate accident damage to personnel and the Ore Flow facility.
Provide expertise and Support in Directing and controlling the operation of Upper and lower Ore Flow to optimizeore crushing and transport from the Grasberg and U/G mines to the Concentrator stockpiles. Ensure the Ore Flowprocess runs smoothly and meets production targets set by the company.
Provide expertise and support in directing and controlling Waste Stacker, lime Plant and limestoneCrushing Operations and Produce lime which meets the quality and quantity standards set by theConcentrator.
Ensure that Ore Flow meets availability and production targets in a safe and environmentally friendly manner.
Ensure that the Ore Flow short term projects are in line with the long terms project and to ensure all capitalexpenditures Within Ore Flow Operations are met the budget and achieve the desired outcome, and do not exceed theapproved amounts.
Provide information and direction for optimization and upgrades, which are accomplished in a timely and satisfactorymanner. Stay abreast of new technology and take advantage of opportunities that improve production, quality, cost,safety and environmental performance.
Provide mentoring in all competencies to develop his peers and high potential employees to improve employee skilllevels.
Provide expertise to assist the Ore Flow Operation in trouble shooting and finding solutions to problems that impactproduction.
Qualifications:
Bachelor’s (S1) Degree in Engineering with minimum (10) ten years to (15) fifteen years experience in crushing and conveying systems, or Operational experience from (15) fifteen years to (20) twenty years experience with in-depth and broad knowledge in crushing and conveying technology.
Strong analytical thinking, customer service and achievement orientation.
Strong knowledge and experience in Project Scoping to ensure the project is well defined, planned and executed to accomplish project objectives.
Ability to manage multiple projects at one time.
Strong knowledge in mining and mineral processing technology.
Ability to work in a culturally large diversified workforce.
Must speak fluent English.
Benefits: Begin first day of employment
Medical, Dental and Vision Insurance.
Relocation assistance/Expatriate Incentives.
